        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 8 at 11:52PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 1151 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Boomer, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Boomer...
Windy Gap...
Moravian Falls...
and Elkville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
